-- Ambac posts first-quarter loss
-- 
-- Wed Apr 23, 2008 6:39am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/23/us-ambac-results-idUSWNAS899820080423

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Ambac Financial Group Inc ABK.N, a bond insurer that struggled to raise capital earlier this year, posted a first-quarter loss on Wednesday after losses of $1.73 billion on credit derivative exposures. 

 The New York-based company posted a loss of $1.66 billion, or $11.69 a share, compared with year-earlier net income of $213.3 million, or $2.02 a share. (Reporting by Christopher Kaufman and  Dan Wilchins ; Editing by Lisa Von Ahn)